timeline.bodyText:
Right now sub-classes are use ctor if it's single message, otherwise directly setting this.message in their own ctor. And all sub-classes are taking responsibility of formatting messages.
We can make things simpler.

knowledge of error message --> json formatting abstraction can be limited to this class. This class can take in single/array of plain error strings. Sub-classes don't need to bother with knowledge of json formatting (and adhering to it)
here in this ctor:

if (!Array.isArray(messages)) {
  messages = [messages]
}
this.jsonError = {
    _status: {
      messages: messages.map(m => { return {message: m}; }),
    },
  };

('message' is being used in 5-6 different contexts, becoming confusing. We can use different variable names, hence 'jsonError')

3 other fns in this class can be deleted

In sub-classes:

no change in badRequestError, httpError, notFoundError
dbError can have boolean isDbConnectionError. It can be set in ctor.
invalidArgumentError

// Plain ctor like other errors. If any api wants to throw custom error messages on invalid argument, it can directly use ctor.

// factory method to help common case
static forParams(badParams) {
  if(!Array.isArray(badParams) {
    badParam = [badParams];
  }
  return new InvalidArgumentError(badParams.map(p => `${httpErrorMessages.INVALID_ARGUMENT}${message}`));
}

